  "risk_regime": {
    "stance": "risk_on",
    "conviction": 68,
    "rationale": "Eight of ten members are explicitly risk_on (Yahya 85, Dixon 85, Kominers 80, Jennings 72, Lazzarin 70, Wuollet 70, Rosenthal 70, Matsuoka 45); the two abstentions (Thaler, Roughgarden) are researchers who decline market calls (no_view), not bears. The consensus posture is STRUCTURAL builder-optimism \u2014 conviction in long-horizon protocol/technology theses through the bear market ('still early', bottom-of-cycle building) \u2014 explicitly paired with acute NEAR-TERM caution on US regulation, CeFi/custodial intermediaries, and uncollateralized/issuer-sold tokens. Conviction set at 68 (below the bullish members' mean) to reflect the two principled abstentions and the near-unanimous regulatory overhang.",
    "provenance": "grounded"
  },
  "notes": "Consensus weighted by BOTH coverage and conviction; conviction damped where members split. (1) Strongest signals are the high-coverage, zero-dispersion blocks: ZK (coverage 14), DeFi (6) and ETH (6) on the bullish side, and crypto-policy-regulation (coverage 5, mean 87.6) as the dominant shared concern. (2) Two items with real coverage are genuinely SPLIT and recorded near-neutral despite decent mean conviction: incentive-design (dispersion 0.98) and governance-dao (0.87); BTC is similarly split among tokens. The apparent dispersion in ZK and ETH is NOT directional disagreement \u2014 it comes from Thaler's ZK security caveats and Roughgarden's neutral analytical ETH/BTC notes, which we preserve as caveats rather than letting them cancel the bullish thesis. (3) Lone high-conviction views were faded out per the coverage rule: single-member items like decentralization (97), dao-legal-entities (88), cex-proof-of-reserves (88), decentralized-verification (88) are real but not house consensus, so omitted or kept at low weight; the strongest are noted as reinforcing adjacent multi-coverage themes. (4) Token signal is thin desk-wide \u2014 most members are infrastructure/research/legal voices who rarely make price calls \u2014 so only ETH carries broad support; other tokens are lone reads retained at low conviction. (5) No items were invented; all names reuse members' exact item labels."
}